-- ── Grok ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Grok is xAI's conversational AI chatbot, available on the web at grok.com, in X, and via iOS and Android apps, with free and paid SuperGrok subscription tiers.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium subscription plus usage-based API pricing$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free; paid plans from $10/month (SuperGrok Lite)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2023, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Palo Alto, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Grok Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Grok review covering xAI's chatbot, Grok 4.5 models, free vs SuperGrok pricing tiers, API costs, features, pros, cons and top AI chatbot alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Grok is the conversational AI chatbot built by xAI, the artificial intelligence company Elon Musk incorporated in Nevada on March 9, 2023 and publicly launched on July 12, 2023 with a team of AI researchers recruited from DeepMind, OpenAI and other leading AI labs, with a stated mission focused on advancing scientific discovery and understanding the universe. Grok itself first shipped in November 2023 as a feature exclusive to X Premium subscribers, tightly integrated into the X (formerly Twitter) platform that Musk also owns, distinguishing it from competitors like ChatGPT and Gemini by giving it real-time access to X's live post feed and a deliberately more irreverent, less filtered conversational personality. The model and product evolved quickly: Grok-1.5 arrived in March 2024 with an expanded 128,000 token context window, Grok-2 launched in beta in August 2024 for Premium and Premium+ subscribers, and in December 2024 xAI made Grok available to free X users for the first time, albeit with usage limits, while simultaneously releasing standalone Grok web and iOS apps in beta, initially limited to Australia. Worldwide availability of the standalone apps followed on January 9, 2025, formally separating Grok from a pure X-Premium perk into an independent product family accessible via grok.com and dedicated mobile apps. Grok 3 launched in February 2025, followed by Grok 4 in July 2025, and xAI added an image and video generation capability called Grok Imagine in July 2025, expanding Grok from a text chatbot into a broader multimodal AI product; Grok 4.5 followed in mid-2026. xAI's financial trajectory has been extraordinarily fast even by AI industry standards: after a 134.7 million dollar seed round in December 2023, the company raised a 6 billion dollar Series B at a 24 billion dollar valuation in May 2024, a 6 billion dollar Series C at a 50 billion dollar valuation in December 2024, roughly 10 billion dollars in equity at a 200 billion dollar valuation in September 2025, and was reportedly targeting a 15 billion dollar raise at a 230 billion dollar pre-money valuation in a Series E round in December 2025, alongside a 5 billion dollar debt facility arranged by Morgan Stanley; total primary funding raised is estimated at over 22 billion dollars, with backers including Sequoia Capital, Andreessen Horowitz and Valor Equity Partners. Ownership structure has shifted twice in dramatic fashion: in March 2025, xAI acquired X in an all-stock transaction that valued xAI at roughly 80 billion dollars and X at roughly 33 billion dollars, folding Musk's social network directly into the AI company, and then in February 2026 SpaceX, also controlled by Musk, acquired xAI, bringing Grok, X and SpaceX under increasingly consolidated ownership. xAI's headquarters is at 1450 Page Mill Road in Palo Alto, California, with an additional office in San Francisco's Mission District (in what was previously OpenAI's own headquarters building) and a large compute buildout centered on the Colossus supercomputer cluster in Memphis, Tennessee. From a product standpoint, Grok is positioned as a general-purpose conversational AI assistant that can answer questions, write and debug code, analyze images, reason through complex problems, and, through Grok Imagine, generate images and video from text prompts, competing directly with OpenAI's ChatGPT, Google's Gemini and Anthropic's Claude. Its most distinctive differentiator remains its deep, native integration with real-time data from X, giving Grok access to live commentary and breaking news other assistants must retrieve through separate search tools, alongside a brand personality that leans into humor and a self-described willingness to answer edgier questions that some competitors decline. Pricing is split across two parallel but overlapping paths as of 2026: a free tier available directly at grok.com or through basic X access offering roughly 10 prompts every two hours on a lighter model; SuperGrok Lite at 10 dollars per month, a lower-cost standalone tier introduced in March 2026 sitting between free and full SuperGrok; SuperGrok at 30 dollars per month or 300 dollars per year, the primary standalone consumer subscription with access to Grok's flagship models; and SuperGrok Heavy at 300 dollars per month, the top consumer tier with guaranteed access to xAI's most capable model at all times. In parallel, X bundles Grok access into its own subscriptions: X Premium at 8 dollars per month includes basic Grok access alongside X platform perks, while X Premium+ at 40 dollars per month bundles fuller Grok access with an ad-free X experience and higher usage throughput. For businesses, xAI offers a Grok Business plan priced at 30 dollars per user per month, and developers can access Grok programmatically through xAI's API, priced per million tokens and varying by model, with the flagship Grok 4.5 priced at roughly 2 dollars per million input tokens (0.50 dollars for cached input) and 6 dollars per million output tokens as of mid-2026. Grok's core competitive set includes ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude and Meta AI, and it differentiates primarily through its real-time X data integration, its unusually rapid model release cadence funded by one of the largest capital raises in AI industry history, and its increasingly tight integration with Musk's other companies, X and SpaceX, following the 2025 and 2026 ownership consolidations.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '8b23fc94-f6ee-4551-9707-24f01eb5e9e4';

